# Fragrance library governance (must-follow)

Before adding, importing, renumbering, editing, retiring, or exposing fragrance data, read:

- `docs/fragrance-library-data-model.md`
- `docs/adding-a-fragrance.md`
- `docs/fragrance-field-map.md`
- `docs/fragrance-import.md`
- `public/Brandsamor_16_Fragrance_Database_JSON.txt` (authoritative governance rules)

## Non-negotiables

- Never renumber a fragrance after creation.
- Never reuse a retired fragrance number.
- Retire/deactivate instead of deleting.
- Preserve historical supplier variants and compliance document versions.
- Never overwrite `ORIGINAL_REFERENCE` note pyramids when adding supplier-confirmed or Brandsamor-observed notes.
- Never expose internal supplier/procurement/testing fields through public APIs or client bundles.
- Never represent missing compliance files as verified/available.
- Imports must be idempotent and must not create duplicates.

